<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Measures 1, 7-9: Em root position open (E-B-E-G pattern in LH, P4/P5 spacing)
- Measure 3-4: G and C with standard "33" root position in RH, open "334" in LH
- Measure 6: Rapid harmonic rhythm (G-C-Am-Em), each beat a new chord — RH 2-note thirds, LH 3-note open
- Final (m9): Full Em spread voicing; RH adds high E5 for resonance

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH consistently uses 2 notes (never crowding melody); LH uses 3-4
- Measure 2: RH broken arpeggio while LH sustains provides rhythmic interest
- Measure 5: LH ascending arpeggio against RH sustained chord — Tchaikovsky sweep texture
- Measure 6: Contrary motion between RH (descending step motion) and LH (root motion)

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-2: Sparse opening, Em tonic establishment
- mm. 3-4: More harmonic motion, G-D-C movement, fuller LH
- mm. 5-6: RH/LH arpeggios peak, four-chord measure 6 brings maximum variety
- mm. 7-8: Sequence of Em-related harmonies, chromatic tension (F#°)
- m. 9: Convergent whole-note cadence, full resonant Em voicing
-->
